  "text": "# Java Class Loading Delegation Chain in OpenJDK\n\n## Overview\nThe Java class loading delegation chain implements a hierarchical, parent-first delegation model where class loaders delegate to their parent before attempting to load a class themselves.\n\n## Key Files and Components\n\n### 1. Java-level Delegation: ClassLoader.java\n**File**: `src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java` (lines 534-570)\n\nThe `loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method implements the parent-first delegation pattern:\n- Checks if the class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass(name)`\n- If not found, delegates to the parent class loader via `parent.loadClass(name, false)`\n- If parent is null, calls `findBootstrapClassOrNull(name)` to search bootstrap classes\n- Only if the parent returns null, calls `findClass(name)` to load the class locally\n- Records statistics via PerfCounter for parent delegation time and find class time\n- If resolve is true, calls `resolveClass(c)`\n\n### 2. Built-in Class Loaders: BuiltinClassLoader.java\n**File**: `src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java` (lines 89-150)\n\nThe `BuiltinClassLoader` extends `SecureClassLoader` and serves as the base class for all three built-in loaders (bootstrap, platform, and application). Key characteristics:\n- Uses modular class loading: maps class names to package names\n- Implements `loadClassOrNull(String cn, boolean resolve)` method (lines 589-631) that:\n  - Checks if the class is already loaded\n  - Finds the candidate loaded module for the class\n  - If the module is in this loader, loads from the module\n  - Otherwise delegates to the parent loader\n  - If not found in parent and module system is initialized, searches the class path\n- Overrides the parent delegation model to handle module-aware class loading\n- Registers as parallel-capable for concurrent class loading\n\n### 3. Built-in Class Loaders Creation: ClassLoaders.java\n**File**: `src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java` (lines 45-187)\n\nThe `ClassLoaders` class creates and manages the three built-in class loaders:\n\n**BootClassLoader** (lines 131-140):\n- Extends BuiltinClassLoader\n- Parent: null (no parent)\n- No class path (bcp = null)\n- Overrides `loadClassOrNull(String cn, boolean resolve)` to delegate to `JLA.findBootstrapClassOrNull(cn)`\n- Used to find resources in modules defined to the boot class loader\n\n**PlatformClassLoader** (lines 146-155):\n- Extends BuiltinClassLoader\n- Parent: BootClassLoader\n- Named \"platform\"\n- Uses class path for JDK modules not in bootstrap\n\n**AppClassLoader** (lines 161-187):\n- Extends BuiltinClassLoader\n- Parent: PlatformClassLoader\n- Named \"app\"\n- Uses application class path (java.class.path)\n- Supports dynamic class path additions via instrumentation\n\nStatic initialization (lines 62-99) creates these loaders and sets up the module system.\n\n### 4. HotSpot Native Implementation: classLoader.cpp\n**File**: `src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp` (lines 1-150)\n\nThe C++ implementation file contains:\n- Performance counter definitions for tracking class loading metrics\n- Native entry points for jimage.dll (Java image file format)\n- Support for path canonicalization\n- Global performance counters for various class loading stages:\n  - Class initialization time\n  - Class verification and linking time\n  - Parent delegation vs. class finding time\n  - Bootstrap, system, and application class loading time\n\n### 5. System Dictionary: systemDictionary.hpp\n**File**: `src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp` (lines 1-100)\n\nThe `SystemDictionary` class is a static utility class that:\n- Maintains a concurrent hash table (Dictionary) per ClassLoaderData\n- Caches all loaded classes initiated or defined by class loaders\n- Implements `resolve_or_fail()` and `resolve_or_null()` methods for looking up or loading classes\n- Uses the SystemDictionary_lock for synchronizing additions to dictionaries\n- Manages placeholders to detect ClassCircularityErrors during loading\n- Stores entries only when classes are completely loaded\n- Supports safe concurrent reads on loaded classes\n\n## Delegation Chain Sequence\n\nThe complete delegation chain for class loading (documented in systemDictionaryShared.cpp lines 390-399):\n\n1. **SystemDictionaryShared::find_or_load_shared_class()** - HotSpot C++ layer\n2. **JVM_FindLoadedClass()** - JNI entry point\n3. **ClassLoader.findLoadedClass()** - Java layer checking loaded classes\n4. **BuiltinClassLoader.loadClassOrNull()** - Module-aware loading with delegation\n5. **BuiltinClassLoader.loadClass()** - Throws exception if not found\n6. **ClassLoaders$AppClassLoader.loadClass()** or **ClassLoaders$PlatformClassLoader.loadClass()** - Specific loader implementations\n\n## Key Design Principles\n\n1. **Parent-First Delegation**: A class loader always delegates to its parent before attempting to load a class itself\n2. **Modular Class Loading**: BuiltinClassLoader maps packages to modules and can delegate directly to the correct loader\n3. **Three-Tier Hierarchy**:\n   - Bootstrap Loader (null parent): Load core JDK classes from modules\n   - Platform Loader (parent: Bootstrap): Load platform modules\n   - Application Loader (parent: Platform): Load application classes\n4. **Caching with SystemDictionary**: All loaded classes are cached by the SystemDictionary for fast lookup\n5. **Concurrent Safety**: Uses parallel-capable loaders and proper locking to support concurrent class loading\n"
